President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 1, 2016, as Loyalty Day in the United States. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of unity and shared ideals in the country's history. He encourages citizens to remember that what defines them as Americans is their dedication to common ideals, rather than their differences in origin or creed. Loyalty Day is meant to recognize the American spirit of loyalty and the sacrifices made for the nation. The President calls upon all Americans to support this national observance by displaying the flag or pledging allegiance to the Republic.